6 15.1-09.1-02.1. Regional education association - Services to be offered.
7 1. In order toTo be eligible for state funding, a regional education association mustshall
8 offer the following services to its member districts:
9 a. Coordination and facilitation of professional development activities for teachers
10 and administrators employed by its member districts;
11 b. Supplementation of technology support services;
12 c. Assistance with achieving school improvement goals identified by the
13 superintendent of public instruction;
14 d. Assistance with the collection, analysis, and interpretation of student
15 achievement data; and
16 e. Assistance with the expansion and enrichment of curricular offerings.
17 2. Subsection 1 does not preclude a regional education association from offering
18 additional services, including services to a district that is not a member of the regional
19 education association.
20 3. A regional education association may enter a contract with the superintendent of
21 public instruction to offer services.
